SIMPLE: transient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transient
<hw>Tran"sient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>transiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>transire</ets>,
<ets>transitum</ets>, to go or pass over. See <er>Trance</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Passing before the sight or perception, or, as it were,
moving over or across a space or scene viewed, and then disappearing;
hence, of short duration; not permanent; not lasting or durable; not
stationary; passing; fleeting; brief; transitory; <as>as,
<ex>transient</ex> pleasure</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Measured this
<xex>transient</xex> world.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hasty; momentary; imperfect; brief; <as>as, a
<ex>transient</ex> view of a landscape</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Staying for a short time; not regular or permanent;
<as>as, a <ex>transient</ex> guest; <ex>transient</ex>
boarders</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Transient</er>, <er>Transitory</er>,
<er>Fleeting</er>.</syn> <usage> <xex>Transient</xex> represents a thing
as brief at the best; <xex>transitory</xex>, as liable at any moment to
pass away. <xex>Fleeting</xex> goes further, and represents it as in the
act of taking its flight. Life is <xex>transient</xex>; its joys are
<xex>transitory</xex>; its hours are <xex>fleeting</xex>.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What is loose love? A <qex>transient</qex> gust.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If [we love] <qex>transitory</qex> things, which soon decay,⟦br⟧
Age must be loveliest at the latest day.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O <qex>fleeting</qex> joys⟦br⟧
Of Paradise, dear bought with lasting woes.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Tran"sient*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Tran"sient*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Transient
<hw>Tran"sient</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which remains but for a
brief time.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transiliency</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Transilience</ent>⟦br⟧
